y also review the nature of the legislature, the governor, the courts, and public authorities as well as how these institutions play a role in making decisions. Finally, the impact of politics is analyzed for the policy areas of intergovernmental fiscal relations, welfare, health, and local education. The sixth edition of Governing New York State provides an excellent summary of the political process and most of the major policy controversies in the state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aNew York (State) -- Economic policy. 0aNew York (State) -- Politics and government -- 1951-. 0aNew York (State) -- Social policy. 0aPublic administration -- New York (State). 4aNew York/Regional : New York State Government. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : State and Local Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / State.2bisacsh1 aBenjamin, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenjamin, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyd, Donald J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDadayan, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuncombe, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGais, Thomas L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalsey, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenderson, Keith M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Cathy M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKersh, Rogan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraus, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorley, Alicen R., econtri